e are no requirements on the language for your Profiler UI’s process, why not pick a language that’s concise and simple?","pos":[4890,5048]},{"pos":[5054,5072],"content":"Windows RT devices","linkify":"Windows RT devices","nodes":[{"content":"Windows RT devices","pos":[0,18]}]},{"content":"Windows RT devices are quite locked down.","pos":[5074,5115]},{"content":"Third-party profilers simply cannot be loaded on such devices.","pos":[5116,5178]},{"content":"This document focuses on Windows 8 PCs.","pos":[5179,5218]},{"pos":[5223,5253],"content":"Consuming Windows Runtime APIs","linkify":"Consuming Windows Runtime APIs","nodes":[{"content":"Consuming Windows Runtime APIs","pos":[0,30]}]},{"content":"In a number of scenarios discussed in the following sections, your Profiler UI desktop application needs to consume some new Windows Runtime APIs.","pos":[5255,5401]},{"content":"You’ll want to consult the documentation to understand which Windows Runtime APIs can be used from desktop applications, and whether their behavior is different when called from desktop applications and Windows Store apps.","pos":[5402,5624]},{"content":"If your Profiler UI is written in managed code, there will be a few steps you’ll need to do to make consuming those Windows Runtime APIs easy.","pos":[5626,5768]},{"content":"See the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Managed desktop apps and Windows Runtime<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=271858)</ept> article for more information.","pos":[5769,5897],"source":" See the [Managed desktop apps and Windows Runtime](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=271858) article for more information."},{"pos":[5902,5926],"content":"Loading the Profiler DLL","linkify":"Loading the Profiler DLL","nodes":[{"content":"Loading the Profiler DLL","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"This section describes how your Profiler UI causes the Windows Store app to load your Profiler DLL.","pos":[5928,6027]},{"content":"The code discussed in this section belongs in your Pr